The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Wednesday, January 07, 2004 				 Laloo salvo
																								Patna, Jan. 6 (PTI): Accusing railway minister Nitish Kumar of being involved in irregular appointments in the railways, Rashtriya Janata Dal president Laloo Prasad Yadav today said he would meet Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee to demand a CBI probe into all recruitments made during Kumars tenure.																								Kumar said the recent leak of question papers for recruitment to Group D posts in the railway was a fit case for a CBI probe.
